\end{pmatrix}
\]

So, \[2A = 
\begin{pmatrix}
  -2 & -4 \\
  -6 & -8
\end{pmatrix}
\]

2. **Tripling **\(B\)**: \[3B = 3 *
\begin{pmatrix}
  1 & 2 \\
