\end{pmatrix}
\]

So, \[3B = 
\begin{pmatrix}
  3 & 6 \\
  9 & 12
\end{pmatrix}
\]

3. **Summing** **\(2A\) and **\(3B\)**: \[2A + 3B =
\begin{pmatrix}
  -2 & -4 \\
  -6 & -8
\end{pmatrix}
+
\begin{pmatrix}
  3 & 6 \\
